questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;The population of 7 villages is shown in the following pie chart.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/23/01/SSC_Akash_Pankaj_126.01.2023_G2.PNG&quot; style=&quot;width: 381px; height: 327px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the population of village C is 4000, what is the total population of all the villages?&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:14px;&quot;&gt;The population of 7 villages in percentage&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:14px;&quot;&gt;The population of village C is 4000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Concept used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:14px;&quot;&gt;Percentage formula = (Value/Total value) &amp;times; 100&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:14px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:14px;&quot;&gt;Population of village C (%) = 4000/Total Population&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 100&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:18px;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:14px;&quot;&gt;8 =&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;4000/Total Population&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 100&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:14px;&quot;&gt;Total population = 4000/8&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 100&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Total population = 50000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;total population of all the villages is 50000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;The graph shows the record of the number of admissions to a certain coaching centre from 2005 to 2010.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/23/01/SSC_Akash_Pankaj_126.01.2023_G1.PNG&quot; style=&quot;width: 450px; height: 259px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
In how many years was the number of admissions greater than that of the previous year?&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;rArr;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Between 2005 - 2006&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; 120 to 170&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;rArr;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Between 2007 - 2008&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; 170 to 270&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;rArr;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;Between 2008 - 2009&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; 270 to 340&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;total of three years.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence the correct answer is option 1).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/11/F1_Mamata_SSC_22.11.22_G12.PNG&quot; style=&quot; width: 456px; height: 266px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following bar graph reflects the income and expenditure of a person in four months.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Savings in January is how much percent less than savings in April?&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Savings = Income - Expenditure&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, savings in January is 1500 - 1468 = Rs 32&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Savings in April is 1820 - 1785&amp;nbsp;= Rs 35&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The difference in savings is 35 - 32 = Rs 3&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So the required percentage is (3 / 35)&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 100 = 8.57 %&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Savings in January is&amp;nbsp;8.57 % less than savings in April&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;The bar graph given here shows the data of the production of cars by three different companies X, Y, Z over the years.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/12/F1_Revannath_SSC_5.11.2022_G1.PNG&quot; style=&quot;width: 350px; height: 212px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For which of the following years is the percentage rise/fall in the production from the previous year the maximum for company Y?&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/12/F1_Revannath_SSC_5.11.2022_G1.PNG&quot; style=&quot;width: 350px; height: 212px;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;rArr;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;For company Y,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Change in production from 2016 to 2017 = 35&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash; 25 =&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;10/25&amp;nbsp;&amp;times; 100 = 40% rise&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Change in production from 2017 to 2018 = 35&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash; 35 = 0, no change&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Change in production from 2018 to 2019 = 40&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash; 35 = 5/35 &amp;times; 100 = 14.28% rise&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Change in production from 2019&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;to 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;= 50&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;ndash; 40&amp;nbsp;= 10/40 &amp;times; 100 = 25% change&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the&amp;nbsp;percentage rise/fall in the production from the previous year the maximum for company Y is in 2017.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;The following bar graph shows the sales (in thousand numbers) of scooters from six different companies in 2011 and 2012.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;//storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/22/12/F1_Revannath_SSC_5.11.2022_G2.PNG&quot; style=&quot;width: 350px; height: 209px;&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The average sales of companies &amp;nbsp;A and E in 2011&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;what percentage of the average sales of companies B and D in 2012?&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Sales of companies B and D in 2012 = 18000 + 21000 = 39,000&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Sales of companies A and E in 2011 = 11000 + 18000 = 29,000&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Percentage composition =&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\frac{29000}{39000}\times 100\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Percentage composition =&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\frac{29}{39}\times 100\)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;= &lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;74.36&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;%&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therefore, the average sales of companies B and D in 2012 is 74.36% of average sales of companies A and E in 2011.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
